$ SQL data type: boolean

According to the → misc/ISO/9075[SQL standared (ISO 9075)], the boolean data type is an optional
→ misc/ISO/9075/features[feature (with ID T031)].

The values that can be assigned to a boolean are
  • `true`
  • `false`
  • → development/databases/SQL/data-types/null[`null`] or `unknown` (unless specified as `not null`)

sa:

  → misc/ISO/9075/features[SQL standard features] E011 (Numeric types) and E021 (Character string types)

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types/bit[The `bit` data type in SQL Server]

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/data-types/boolean[Oracle: boolean data type]

  Although → development/databases/SQLite does → development/databases/SQLite/datatypes/boolean[not have a boolean data type], it understands the keywords
  → development/databases/SQL/data-types/predefined/boolean[`true` and `false`] which evaluate to `1` and `0`, respectively.

  → development/databases/SQL/data-types
